children.value: I'm a multi-disciplinary engineer with a goal of transforming traditional engineering industries using the latest technological advancements in Computer Science. Keen interest in Unmanned Aerial Vehicles, Artificial Intelligence and Software Development. Always open to learning and working opportunities.
-	Teaching Assistant for CS2103/T Software Engineering AY19/20 Sem 1.
-	Conduct tutorials on Software Engineering principles and provide guidance to 2 software engineering project groups.
- Collaborated intra-organization to provide automation solutions for various high volume, rule-based and repetitive tasks, thus freeing up human capital for higher value business functions.
- Tapped on both engineering and computer science knowledge to automated workflow for engineering related business processes.
- Created operational dashboard to monitor the status of the bots.
- Worked on A321 Passenger-to-Freighter Conversion Programme.
- Conducted structural design study of key components in aircraft.
- Reviewed design data, drawing and documents.
- Prepared aircraft technical manuals and stress analysis report.
-	Studying Mechanical Engineering (Aeronautical Specialisation) with a second major in Computer Science
- Relevant coursework: Autonomous Flight of Micro UAVs, Aerospace Design, Propulsion and Power, Computational Modelling
- Relevant coursework: Fluid Mechanics, Thermodynamics, Systems & Feedback
-	Bond free scholarships awarded to high calibre individuals who demonstrate academic excellence, present excellent co-curricular activities record and exhibit outstanding leadership qualities.
- Emerged Second Runner-up in student category after competing with over 500 teams over 3 rounds.
- Find out more about the app in the project section below.
- Finalist in HackDelft 2018 and Category Winner for ORTEC Finance.
